The strong and shaded mound
that leads with quiet confidence
around and away from the side of your chin
carries me carefully on a long and
hopeful journey into the fertile land
near the base of your left earlobe
where the soft and delicate curve
begs to be adored, every so
gently, from behind, much the
way a lioness naps in the shade on a
hot day. The delicate hairs stand to dance
as I breathe, and I sleep beneath the air
that takes me home.

- duane edmonds -
